                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/12–349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-03T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 3, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 3—11:18 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5110. Baeyens has just telephoned to say Massigli has heard that British Cabinet
                    will “pronounce itself” on principle and timing of Chinese Communist recognition
                    week beginning December 12. French Embassy Washington instructed request our
                    views. Baeyens feels this timing leaves narrow margin for consultation.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 5110, repeated London 894.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
